  "text": "Also, from the third row in Figure 11 , we see that 70% of the files and 66% of the bytes have never been recalled. Once data is stored in the archive it is rarely read back, which begs the question if the archive is mainly used for disaster recovery or if the users are unable to find data due to a lack of metadata. OLCF is factoring in these insights in deciding future investments in HPSS development. [CITATION_1] Files less than one year old are calculated from the sum of all the columns to the left of the blue one.",
